&lt;p&gt;Your RTX 4090 started as sand. Actual sand, refined into silicon so pure that only one in a billion atoms is an impurity. That silicon gets sliced into wafers thinner than a human hair, then blasted with ultraviolet light through masks that print transistors smaller than a virus.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>